Actor Bill Nighy stole every scene he was in when he played the aging rock star Billy Mack in the 2003 Christmas rom-com “Love Actually.” But he recently told British GQ that one line in particular has followed him everywhere since the film came out. “When I die, if I get an obituary, it will say: ‘Hey kids, don’t buy drugs. Become a rock star, people give you them for free,’” he said. Nighy said local youths follow him around reciting the line. He even heard it once from a customs inspector at an airport. Nighy breaks down his role in that film and others ― including “Pirates of the Caribbean,” “Underworld” and “The Girl In The Cafe” ― below: (h/t digg)